import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Flight Delays')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'])
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    ax.set_ylabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    origin_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the most common origin airport?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data['date_only'] = data['date'].dt.date
    flight_counts = data['date_only'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    plt.plot(flight_counts.index, flight_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
